Package: rpmviz
Title: Industrial RPM Visualization Tools
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jim", "Zaccardo", , "jim@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A collection of tools for creating industrial-style RPM (Revolutions
    Per Minute) visualizations. Includes circular speed dial displays using the
    circlize package and digital 7-segment style displays. Designed for
    visualizing spindle speeds across multiple pulley configurations, with
    support for material-based optimal speed zones and real-time RPM indicators.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports:
    circlize,
    grDevices,
    graphics
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://github.com/jimzaccardo/Circlize-Package-Prototype
BugReports: https://github.com/jimzaccardo/Circlize-Package-Prototype/issues
